3 Stars Out Of 5



Links could be better


January 13, 2013



Fred
New Hampshire



Age: 35-44
Gender: male
  

Quality:




3
 
Value:




5
 
Meets Expectations:




3
  
            Matthew Henry's concise commentary is a part of my daily bible reading. This book is a great resource that opens up God's words. Great value!


The quality of the ebook could be better, the links are not very navigable. There is a link for every chapter of the bible, this format makes it very difficult to navigate to particular book. For instance, if I want to navigate to Isaiah, I need to scroll through every chapter of the bible from Genesis to Isaiah to get to what I want. There are 126 pages of content links, this makes no sense.


The bible ebook I own has links for each of the 66 books, when you select the book you want you are then navigated to a page to select the chapter. If this commentary had that feature it would get 5 stars.
        














Was this review helpful?
