Notes

Charles is listed by that name alone, or as Charles H in mostcensuses.  The 1900 census has his name as Henry C, though thenext-born child was also named Henry.  His son Ishmael's obituarygives his father's name as Charles Henry Christian."Ishmael Leland "Ish" Christian, Age 82, of Globe, passed awayNovember 16, 2004, at Heritage Health Care Center. He was born inMountain View, Oklahoma on October 3, 1922, the son of Tersal Georgine(Tabor) and Charles Henry Christian. ... Left behind in loving memoryare: his wife of 36 years, Mary E. Christian of Globe, AZ; ...brother, Dwayne Christian of Iowa; sister, Betty Jo Byrd of Willcox,AZ; brother-in-law, Bill Duncan of Catalina, AZ; ... His parents andsister, Billye Duncan preceded him in death."--  Obituary of Ishmael Leland Christian, Unknown Newspaper, Tucson,Arizona, 23 November 2004, http://ancstry.me/UfHMvdHere are the variations of Charles' name I have seen from sources:Henry C - 1900 censusCharles -- uncle Bud Jenkins' list; 1910 censusCharles H -- 1920 census; WWI Draft registration (Charles, But signedC H)Charlie H -- 1930 censusIt is not certain that Henry was also the name of this child.  But thepredominance of sources indicates that the name beginning with the Hwas the middle name, not the first, though he is Henry C in the 1900census.  His younger brother Henry is listed as simply Henry in allcensuses and his uncle's list of children, except the 1930 census forOakdale, Washita County, Oklahoma.  There he is listed as Henry C.Thus we have Charles H and Henry C.  This might explain why the 1900census enumerator got confused on the name of Charles and listed himas Henry C, which seems to be the younger brother's name.  I don'tknow what Henry's initial C stands for nor what Charles' initial Hstands for.1900 Census, Union, Washita County, Oklahoma, District 211, page 13A(147A), Hse/Fam #189Willie Christain [sic] Head W M  Oct 1857 42  Miss England GA FarmerMandy Christain Wife W F  Mar 1858  42  MS MS MSHenry C Christain Son  May 1892  8 [seems to be Charles]  ChickasawInd Terr  England  Miss Farmer1910 Federal Census, Washita County, Oklahoma, 28 April, Oakdale,District 263, page 20B-21A, Hse #309, Fam #390Christian, William G Head M W 60 MS England AL FarmerChristian, Amanda L Wife F W 45 MS GA GAChristian, Charles Son  M W 17 OK MS MS FarmingIn this census the birth place of his father was mis-recorded on everychild's entry, showing England, which was their grandfather'sbirthplace.  Charles' father William James was born in Mississippi.World War I Draft Registration Cards, 1917-1918Charles ChristianResidence Washita County, OklahomaBirth 17 Nov 1893 OklahomaOccupation Self-Employed Farmer, SingleMedium Height, Slender, Brown Eyes, Black HairRegistered 5 June 1917 in Washita County, OKSigned C H ChristianIn 1920, Charles and his wife Teresa (listed as Treason in the census)are living in the same household with his parents William and Amanda,whose household also includes two other sons and their wives.1920 Federal Census, Washita County, Oklahoma, 15 January, Oakdale,District 192, page 4B, Hse #65, Fam #65Christian, William J Head M W 70 MS England AL FarmerChristian, Amanda L Wife F W 60 MS GA GAChristian, Charles H Son  M W 27 OK MS MS FarmingChristian, Treason [Teresa?]  Dau-in-law [Wife of Charles]  F W 17 TXMS MSIn 1930 Charles is listed as Charlie H, and is still living in OakdaleTownship, Washita County, Oklahoma, where he grew up.  His mother isliving next door to him, alone as a window.  She is listed as Mandy MChristian.  Her middle initial M is a puzzle, since she is listed asAmanda L or Lucinda  or Mandy, or as Lucinda Amanda, in varioussources.1930 Federal Census, Washita County, Oklahoma, 15 April, OakdaleTownship, District 17, page 9A, Hse #156, Fam #168Christian, Charlie H  Head  M W 36 married at age 25  Okla Miss MissFarmerChristian, Tresa  Wife F W 26 married at age 15  Tex Miss MissChristian, Billie  Dau F W 9 Okla Okla TexasChristian, Ishmal  Son M W 7 Okla Okla Texas[This name is poorly formed, and ink uneven, but it is not Johnias, asAncestry.com transcribes.  First two letters most match Is in othernames/words]Christian, Bettie J  Dau F W  mos Okla Okla Texas [born in June 1929]In 1935, Charles and Tresel were reported in the Tuscon CityDirectory, as well as Charles' brother Oscar, for whom a wife is notreported.U.S. City Directories, 1822-1995Tucson, Arizona, City Directory, 1935, p 193Christian Oscar C lino opr r 1333 E 10th stChristian Chas H (Tresel) attdt Vets Hosp h 240 E Ft Lowell rd1940 Federal Census, Pima County, California, 20 April, Tucson,District 10-55, page 18B, 240 Lowell Rd, Hse #473, Owns $300Christian, Charles Head M W 47 Married Grade 7 Oklahoma same place in1935 No Occup [b abt 1893]Christian, Tresel Wife M W 37 Married Grade H1 b Texas  same place in1935 [b abt 1903]Christian, Ishmael Son M W 17 Single Grade H3 Oklahoma same place in1935 [b abt 1923]Christian, Betty Jo Dau F W 10 Single Grade 5 Oklahoma same place in1935 [b abt 1930]Charles and Tresel were listed agian in the 1941 Tuscon CityDirectory.  His brother Oscar is not included this time.U.S. City Directories, 1822-1995Tucson, Arizona, City Directory, 1941, p 96Christian Chas H (Tresel) 240 E Ft Lowell rd rearThe date of birth in the Social Security records is one year laterthat reported in Charles' WWI Draft registration.Social Security Death IndexCharles ChristianNo residence address reportedBorn 17 Nov 1894Died Aug 1964SSN 527-18-0075 issued Arizona (Before 1951)Charles H ChristianBirth Nov. 17, 1894Death Aug. 17, 1964Daughter Bette Jo Christian Byrd (1929 - 2014)Inscription: Oklahoma, PVT 131 Machine Gun BN, WWIBurial Sunset Cemetery, Willcox, Cochise County, ArizonaCreated by Diane & John Sep 18, 2009--  Find A Grave Memorial #42098316,http://www.findagrave.com/cgi-bin/fg.cgi?page=gr&GRid=42098316

 

